Consider the following C program:

#include <stdio.h>

int g(int n) {
    return (n + 10);
}

int f(int n) {
    return g(n * 2);
}

int main() {
    printf("%d", f(f(3)));
    return 0;
}

The output of the C program is __________ (Answer in integer)

Show the activation records and the display structure just after the procedures called at lines marked z and y have started their execution. Be sure to indicate which of the two procedures named A you are referring to.

Program Test;
  var x : integer;
  Procedure A;
    var y : integer;
    Procedure B;
      var z : integer;
      begin
        ...... (*z*)
      end B;
    begin
      y := A;
      ...... (*y*)
    end A;
  begin
    x := B;
    call A;
  end Test.

Which of the following correctly describes the display structure when execution is at line marked z (inside B, called from A, which was called from Test)?

A. Display[0] = Test AR, Display[1] = A AR, Display[2] = B AR
B. Display[0] = B AR, Display[1] = A AR, Display[2] = Test AR
C. Display[1] = Test AR, Display[2] = A AR
D. Display[0] = Test AR, Display[1] = B AR
